# Git workflow

When you finish a change in this repo:

1. Commit only the files related to the work you just completed (do not include unrelated local changes).
2. Push to `main` on `origin` without being asked again.
3. Use a concise commit message focused on why the change was made.

Do not skip the push step after completing work unless the user explicitly says not to push.
